snippet.textDisplay:
I sincerely hope you see this, Steve. ...to have one more person to say that “it’s ok,” and to know you’re not alone in your fight.

You make so many of us laugh with every video; we look forward to them, and rewatch them when we need a smile. But... I know all too often it may be the ones that seem the happiest, most comedic, or put together that are struggling inside; I also personally understand this feeling entirely too well.

First, I must say that you’re incredibly brave for sharing. You absolutely didn’t need to apologize, let alone share as to why. It makes me so sad to hear that your bipolar can get to be so debilitating at times. I’ve been there multiple times with depression, and am currently dealing with several forms of anxiety so severe that help feed the depression and have had me down for the count for a few years now, to be honest.

I’ve heard SO many stories of how 2019 was such a bad year for so many people, and even though that may just be a drop in the bucket, I hope this new year finds you in better health.

snippet.textDisplay: Thanks for being so open about your mental health Steve, it encourages conversations about it which is really positive. I've struggled with my mental health all my life and am so encouraged by how much more open the subject is now compared to twenty years ago. When I was in my twenties noone would ever talk about it let alone admit to having MH problems and I was frequently penalised in jobs for having to take time off due to it. Thankfully I now work for a company who champions MH and have a very supportive manager. I hope for the same for everyone living with MH. Take as long as you need Steve, best wishes to you and your awesome animals x

snippet.textDisplay:
Greetings fellow bipolaroid! Looks like you are more prone to the depressive side than the manic......count your blessings! If I could be so bold, please do yourself the biggest favor ever and seek treatment. I waited waaaaay too long and made more problems for myself than Sylvester has made for you, impulse control blah blah blah.

PS, for us, standard anti depressants are nothing more than crystal meth, avoid them at all costs. I was misdiagnosed, put on Wellbutrin and got two hours of sleep a day for almost six months, not fun. When properly treated with meds and most importantly, good therapy and counseling, life is so much better! Best of luck and thank you for sharing your great stories.

snippet.textDisplay:
Steve, I'm really glad to see you back online because I know that it means that you're feeling at least a little bit better. We really appreciate your videos and if you need time to take care of yourself, we all fully understand and support you.
I know from personal experience that it is NOT easy to care for your family when you are depressed--especially the furry one's who literally rely on you to survive and thrive. When I get depressed, I tend to forget the litter boxes. Then when they get full after a day or three, I get even more depressed because my perception of failure tends to make me feel like the pain and depression are somehow deserved...then it just snowballs.

I do understand that bipolar is not the same as severe depression, but the symptoms are often similar and different points...I'm just glad that you've gotten a diagnosis and are managing to not only maintain your levels of dysfunction, but you are able to care for your babies and to get your movies out here for the rest of us. Thank you so much for all your time and effort into this because nothing makes me feel better than my own cats.

Dude, if you ever need to talk, you can always message me. I'm not going to judge you, or any dumb shit like that...I know how it feels and just want to make sure that you have support if you need it. I know that when you are in the throes of bullshit depression, having people care about you usually doesn't mean shit, but sometimes it does, and if you need support, just get in touch...hell, you can always stop by my fiance's stream on twitch (you can message me for his name and stuff because I'm not going to spam your channel like that)...that way you don't have to be bummed alone, you can listen to me bitching in the background (quite like Sylvester even!)
Just thank you Steve, for bringing Talking Kitty into our lives, and for just being you--the honesty and openness gives support to others who are feeling ya. hugs from me and my fam. And ummm...can ya give Shelby and the gang some hugs from us too?
